@startuml use-cases-data-lifecycle
title trawhile — Data Lifecycle (Epic 8)

note as N
  Epic 8 is fully automated — no UI interaction required.

  Retention periods and node retention are configured via
  the system config file (SR-088).

  Activity purge (F8.3) runs nightly at 23:59 (company
  timezone), deleting whatever crossed the rolling retention
  cutoff as of that night. Node deletion (F8.4) runs
  immediately after each nightly activity purge. Both jobs
  are idempotent and resume on application restart using
  stored cutoff_date.

  See state-purge-lifecycle.puml for entity lifecycle states
  and cross-entity deletion dependencies.
end note

@enduml
